        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 4:33PM PDT by NWS Sacramento CA</headline>
        <description>At 432 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Dana, moving southwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Dana, Fall River Mills, Mcarthur, and Glenburn.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
